      <div class="msgContentFrame">I'm the type of guy who doesn't like to use any more UI mods than I really need to, I dislike the whole hassle of having to update them after most patches, and I don't like using .exe clients (like the curse client) for obvious reasons; I guess I'm just paranoid about them. <br /> <br />Either way, there's this annoying &quot;feature&quot; with the minimap that is simply starting to drive me nuts. I was just talking to my mom about this (she's playing WoW right now, and had it occur to her). <br /> <br />For some reason or other, the Minimap insists on zooming in, and neither one of us can figure out why. We like to keep it zoomed out to the maximum. Sometimes it is when we enter buildings or caves, and it will stay zoomed in, but yet other times it doesn't. Sometimes, we log on, and the map is zoomed into to maximum, even though it wasn't when we logged out last. Is there a way to get it to stop doing this? <br /> <br />Another UI annoyance, is for some reason, when I log on, the Character and Keyring Buttons are flashing on and off as if I got a new pet or key, even though I did not. A minor annoyance, but again, I can't find a pattern to it. Sometimes it happens, sometimes it doesn't... does it do this to anyone else? <br /> <br />And lastly, the worst offender... looting. Why is it, with Auto-Loot, sometimes the character absolutely refuses to loot quest items, even when solo and not in a group? You'll right click the corpse, the loot window comes up and..... nothing happens. The loot isn't taken. Click it again.... nope. Use an ability to see if you got lag? No lag, it happens instantly. WTF. <br /> <br />Sometimes it takes 4, 5 tries to actually get loot out of a loot pool, but only if it contains a quest item, or item that starts a quest. <br /> <br />The only addons I use are TitanPanel, GoGo Mount, Armory, and Loremaster/Everyquest (though I think those two aren't loading as they are showing up as &quot;outdated&quot;). <br /> <br />Anyone have this happen to them, or better yet, know how to fix these annoyances?</div>
