      <div class="msgContentFrame">I am using something called sexymap (Or something similar - I don't honestly recall the exact name) and I have the exact opposite experience. <br /> <br />My map stays zoomed out all the time - then, I can scroll over the minimap and 'mouse roll' (like google maps) to zoom in.  *Say for example you are looking for a quest-giver and you can't tell from the zoomed out map if he is in the building to the left or slightly north and to the left....  You can mouse-over...  Roll the mouse and the screen moves in. <br /> <br />Then - when you start running around again the map sets itself to MAX range (Max zoom out).   <br /> <br />I find it helpful and easy to use.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Most things you worry about never happen anyway.</div></div>
